description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, Peggy-O, Walkin' Blues, Ramble On Rose, Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues, The Music Never Stopped-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Playin' In The Band-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Space-> I Need A Miracle-> Stella Blue-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

reviews.review_text: Thank you tapers! Another Charlie Miller beauty I don't need to speak much on the show itself, which is a real stellar outing through and through. For my money, this is easily a top 5 of 1990. Top 10 of '89-90. Hell, you can even just look at the setlist to figure that one out. But what I really want to review here is just how crisp and clean the sound on this recording is! I can't believe this one's been up almost 4 years now and hardly anyone has touched it. By far the most sonically pleasing source of this wonderful show. I'm no mixing engineer, but I know what a great Grateful Dead show sounds like, and this is IT. Ted, incredible job capturing this one. And Charlie, you've mastered the transfer as an art as well as a science. Thank you for allowing one of my all time favorite Dead shows to be heard in such fashion!
